Actually, looking at the todo tests more carefully, I see the `Step` type will need to support `"claim"` operations too, and items will have complex shapes (cursed, enchantment levels, materials). These interfaces will need heavy modification. Adding them now with incomplete knowledge is premature abstraction.

However, the types do make the function signature more intentional -- you can see at a glance what shape the data takes. This is a genuine Rule 2 improvement. The interfaces are small and will be easy to evolve. I'll keep them but verify this is net positive.

